content:
With Scapy you can easily send crafted ARP reply packets. The idea is to constantly send the victim ARP replies telling it we are the router.
We do the same for the router, we tell it we are the victim machine. After we become the man in the middle we can intercept &amp; inspect all data&hellip;
To allow forwarding of packets between the victim and the gateway we need to enable ip_forward:
echo &#39;1&#39; &gt; /proc/sys/net/ipv4/ip_forward The function get_mac sends arp request message (&ldquo;Who has&rdquo;) to the broadcast address, so all clients on the LAN receive it,
we will get the correct mac address back from the target_ip.
Now that we have the correct mac address from the target we can start sending spoofed reply packets with spoof function (&rsquo;target_ip&rsquo; is at &lsquo;attacker mac address&rsquo;)
